    "title": "Dynamic Equilibrium",
    "description": "&quot;Men do not mirror themselves in running water, they mirror themselves in still water. Only what is still can still the stillness of other things.&quot;\n– Zhuangzi\n\n&quot;The doctrines of religion are resolved into carefulness; carefulness into vigorousness; vigorousness into guiltlessness; guiltlessness into abstemiousness; abstemiousness into cleanliness; cleanliness into godliness.&quot;\n– Talmud, Division of Mishna.\n\n&quot;We live in a nightmare of falsehoods, and there are few who are sufficiently awake and aware to see things as they are. Our first duty is to clear away illusions and recover a sense of reality.&quot;\n– Nikolai Berdyaev, 'Political Testament' (1949).",
